'''Bony Dashaco''' (born''' Boniface Abayo Dashaco''' on  1 December 1976)<ref name="mediaafricagroup1">{{cite web|url= http://mediaafricagroup.tripod.com/id7.html |title=Who to contact about what... |publisher=Media Africa Group |accessdate=6 July 2017 }}</ref> is a Cameroonian businessman,<ref name="brandafrica">{{cite web|url= http://www.brandafrica.net/Leadership.aspx|title= LEADERSHIP Board of Trustees |publisher=Enyewah|accessdate=2  July 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.jeuneafrique.com/10146/economie/ils-exportent-le-savoir-faire-camerounais/|title =Ils exportent le savoir-faire camerounais|date= 28 October 2016| accessdate=6  July 2017 }}</ref> who is the chairman of African Center for Marketing, Advertising and Research (ACMAR) media group, which has a presence in 22 African countries with 1000 direct jobs.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://challengepro.cm/2017/05/bony-dashaco-president-directeur-general-acmar-media-group-3/|title=BONY DASHACO : Président-directeur général Acmar Media Group|date= 12 March 2017| accessdate=6  July 2017 }}</ref><ref name="businessincameroon1">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.businessincameroon.com/pdf/BC34.pdf |title=Bony Dashaco: the communicator distributing his messages in 22 African countries |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |magazine=Business in Cameroon |publication-date=January 2016 |volume=34-35 |page=10 |publisher=Stratline Limited |accessdate=2 July 2017 }}</ref>

In  2014, he was nominated as an "African leader of tomorrow" by [[Institut Choiseul for International Politics and Geoeconomics]] as a person below the age of 40 who has impacted society.<ref name="acmar">{{cite web|url= https://cm.usembassy.gov/ambassador-visits-acmar-media-group/|title= Ambassador Visits ACMAR Media Group|date= 24 March 2016| accessdate=2  July 2017 }}</ref><ref name="businessincameroon2">{{cite web|url= http://www.businessincameroon.com/companies/0910-5053-10-cameroonians-named-among-african-leaders-of-tomorrow|title= 10 Cameroonians named among "African leaders of tomorrow"|date= 4 July 2017 |publisher=businessincameroon.com | accessdate=2 July 2017 }}</ref> In October 2016, Institut Choiseul ranked him #36 on the list of top 100 African managers below the age of 40.<ref name="brandafrica" /><ref>http://docplayer.fr/8943396-Les-leaders-economiques-de-demain.html</ref>

==Career==
Dashaco is the president of [[Médiafrique]], an affiliate of [[ACMAR International]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://cameroonnewsagency.com/media-shake-mediafrique-frida-leyina-gets-top-job-new-station-manager-sw/|title =Media: Shake-Up At Mediafrique , Frida Leyina Gets Top Job As New Station Manager For SW|date= 19 June 2017| accessdate=6  July 2017 }}</ref> He was nominated in the 2016 Ranking of 50 Most Influential Young  Cameroonians by the Center for Entrepreneurship, Leadership and Business Management Development (CELBMD) Africa.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.thenigerianvoice.com/news/249739/achaleke-christian-leke-voted-2016-most-influential-young-ca.html|title =Achaleke Christian Leke Voted 2016 Most Influential Young Cameroonian|date= 28  April  2017| accessdate=6  July 2017 }}</ref> In 2016, he was  interviewed  by  [[France]] News Network [[Africa 24]] with a special focus on Africa to highlight the development of media in Africa, and its problems and solutions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.africa24tv.com/fr/linterview-bony-dashaco|title =L'INTERVIEW - BONY DASHACO|date=15 March 2016| accessdate=6  July 2017 }}</ref>

In March 2016, the [[US]] embassy in [[Cameroon]] visited Acmar group in [[Douala]] and had an interview with the group president based on US foreign policy in Cameroon.<ref name="acmar"/>
Dashaco was named one of [[Institut Choiseul for International Politics and Geoeconomics]]'s list of 100 future economic leaders of Africa.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://choiseul.info/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Choiseul-100-Africa-2015-VA.pdf|title=Choiseul Africa Economy leaders  for tomorrow| accessdate=6  July 2017 }}</ref>

==Personal life==
Dashaco is married and has one child.<ref name="brandafrica" />

