{{Use Indian English|date=July 2018}}
'''Vikar Ahmed''' (died 7 April 2015) also known as '''Vikaruddin''' was an activist of the [[Darsgah-Jihad-O-Shahadat]], an affiliate of the Islamic extremist group [[Students Islamic Movement of India]] and also linked to [[Harkat-ul-Jihad al-Islami]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.hindu.com/2008/12/04/stories/2008120458890300.htm | title=What were Vikar and his associates up to? | newspaper=[[The Hindu]] | date=4 December 2008}}</ref> He is a suspect in the [[Mecca Masjid bombing]]. He was absconding from [[Andhra Pradesh]] police<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/police-offer-rs-5-lakh-reward-for-vikaruddin/619802/0 | title=Police offer Rs 5 lakh reward for Vikaruddin | newspaper=Indian Express | date=17 May 2010}}</ref> but was caught in July 2010.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.simplytelangana.com/news/2010/07/13/dreaded-terrorist-vikaruddin-in-police-custody/ | title=Most wanted terrorist Vikaruddin arrested in Hyd | publisher=Simply Telangana | date=13 July 2010}} {{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

He was accused of being involved in the deadly attacks on [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]] police in 2009 and 2010. In the 2009 incident, a policeman was killed and another injured when assailants opened fire at [[Falaknuma]] area of Hyderabad, while in 2010 a policeman was killed and three others were reported injured when two people, riding a motorcycle, opened fire on a police picket at [[Shalibanda]] in the Old City area of Hyderabad.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-138716 | title='Terror attack' kills policeman in Hyderabad | date=16 May 2010 | newspaper=The Daily Star | first=Pallab | last=Bhattacharya | accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref>

Vikaruddin along with four other suspected SIMI activists were killed in an encounter near Alair in Nalgonda district of [[Telangana]] on 7 April 2015 while on their way to Hyderabad Court from Warangal Jail. The five men were killed when one of them attempted to overpower the security personnel escorting them and snatch a weapon in a bid to escape.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.ndtv.com/telangana-news/5-suspected-terrorists-killed-in-encounter-in-telangana-752853 | title=Suspected Terrorists Killed in Encounter in Telangana | publisher=NDTV | date=8 April 2015}}</ref>

